				\begin{document}$${{{{{{\rm{Mn}}}}}}}^{2+}+2{{{{{{\rm{H}}}}}}}_{2}{{{{{\rm{O}}}}}}\;\rightleftharpoons\; {{{{{\rm{MnOOH}}}}}}+3{{{{{{\rm{H}}}}}}}^{+}+{{{{{{\rm{e}}}}}}}^{-}$$\end{document}where Mn2+ comes from MnSO4, a component of the BG11 medium. Some examples of detected pseudo-photocurrents of manganese are shown and described in detail in Supplementary Fig. 23. Therefore, before electrochemical measurements, the pH of cell suspensions was always confirmed to be below approximately 8.0, and when necessary, fresh BG11 or HCl was added not only to adjust the optical density, but also the pH of cell suspensions below approx. 8.0. In chronoamperometry, the applied voltage was fixed to +0.25 V vs. Ag/AgCl, at which sufficient current generation occurred (Supplementary Fig. 24) and a psedo-photocurrent was never detected under an appropriate pH (Supplementary Fig. 23).
